post_text:
The annual Thrive Drive (formally United Way) is ongoing through October 31st, 2020 but already is off to a great start. The drive started on the first of September and here 11 days in has gathered 35% of the hoped for goal of $20,000.

Thrive funds many area non-profit programs and the money donated stays here in Otero and Lincoln counties.

Thank you to all who have donated.

post_text:
Thank you everyone for being patient as we migrate to a new system. Here are some tips that may help you register.
1. When you are asked to enter information exactly, cut and paste so it is exact.
2. When you enter your code and wait for a verification email from PowerSchool, if you do not receive it immediately, do not ask for a new code. This will slow down the process, and when you do receive the code, it will no longer be usable because when you asked for a new code, the old one became invalid.
3. If you do not receive a confirmation email at the completion of your registration, do not worry. If you finished the process, the registration should be finalized.

We hope this helps. Again, we are answering calls live today. We will do our best to answer all calls today. We will be available again on Monday if you do not receive a call.

post_text: Registration for Alamogordo Public Schools will open on Thursday, July 23rd at 8:00 am and continue through Friday, July 24th at 5:00 pm. ALL REGISTRATION, both returning student and new student registration (including kindergarten) will OCCUR ONLINE! This means that you do not need to go to your campus at all to register! Registration should take about ten minutes per child. If you have difficulty registering, a help desk is available for you at helpdesk@alamogordoschools.org. If you can't register online, someone at the help desk will guide you through the process. Also, you will receive an email with an access code that will allow you to join the Parent Portal to register. There is a team available to help you through this process. For more information and to register, please visit alamogordoschools.org
text: Registration for Alamogordo Public Schools will open on Thursday, July 23rd at 8:00 am and continue through Friday, July 24th at 5:00 pm. Registration should take about ten minutes per child. If you have difficulty registering, a help desk is available for you at helpdesk@alamogordoschools.org. Alamogordo High School
May 20 at 9:02 PM ·

Tiger Graduates, Parents, Guardians, and Fans,

Here is the link to our AHS/ADS virtual graduation ceremony scheduled for Friday, 22 May, at 6:00PM:

alamogordo-hs.Stageclip.com

You may share it with as many people as you like, no "tickets" required.

At 8:00PM that same night, we will be holding the drawing for the Perfect Attendance Car, courtesy of Mr. Bobby Martinez and Desert Sun Motors. The drawing will livestream on the Alamogordo High School Facebook page.

And after that, at 8:20PM (2020), we'll have our final Friday Night Lights for the AHS/ADS Classes of 2020, but this time, it won't just be stadium lights--we'll be lighting up the sky above Tiger Stadium with our traditional graduation fireworks!

Thank you for your amazing support of our socially-distanced, "drive-through" commencement week!

GO, TIGERS! GO, FIGHT, WIN!

This Sunday, 17 May 2020 at 6:00PM, a Virtual Baccalaureate Ceremony will be held for AHS Graduating Seniors. A meeting link will be posted here soon.

The baccalaureate is a non-denominational spiritual service that allows for public school graduates to find spiritual meaning that aligns with their personal beliefs. It is NOT a mandatory event.

This year's theme is Perseverance. We're looking for up to four graduates who would like to speak for 3-5 minutes. If interested, please contact Coach Winrow at nathan.winrow@alamogordoschools.org as soon as possible.

post_text:
*Congratulations to Miss Alyssa Montoya, C/O 2020 Senior! Alyssa was selected out of many applicants as this year's recipient of the William Buhler Memorial Scholarship. The William Buhler Memorial Scholarship is established in memory of long time Alamogordo High School history teacher, Mr. Bill Buhler. Mr. Buhler passed away within months of his well-deserved retirement after devoting 31 years to AHS as a passionate, caring, dedicated history teacher.
Alyssa will use her $500 Scholarship to attend the Dona Ana Community College where she will be studying early childhood education. Alyssa strives to be an Elementary Education Teacher in her future.Pictured here are Alyssa Montoya as she receives her scholarship from Mrs. Diane Buhler-Guthrie. Congratulations to Alyssa Montoya!!

Alamogordo High Schools Business Professionals of America (BPA) Chapter has been in Albuquerque competing at the State Leadership Conference this week. Thirteen students competed and eleven of those students were finalists in at least one event. Nine students have qualified for Nationals in May and will hopefully be traveling to National Harbor, Maryland (Just outside of DC).

Congratulations to all who took part. See the results in the picture.

post_text: The Chaparral Middle School FIRST LEGO League teams-- CMS Champions and Tiger Bots-- represented CMS and Alamogordo Public Schools in the New Mexico State FIRST LEGO League Championship in Albuquerque this past weekend on Saturday, February 15, 2020. The event featured 36 teams from around the entire state that had been chosen through previous qualifying rounds. Both CMS teams worked hard to showcase their robotics, core values, and project skills, and The CMS Tiger Bots won the Third Place Championship Award. They have been invited to compete in a yet to be determined international competition in May. Congratulations go out to Coaches Sarah Cerra and Sgt. Maurer and to both FLL Teams for a great job by everyone.

Both CMS teams worked hard to showcase their robotics, core values, and project skills, and The CMS Tiger Bots won the Third Place Championship Award. They have been invited to compete in a yet to be determined international competition in May. Congratulations go out to Coaches Sarah Cerra and Sgt. Maurer and to both FLL Teams for a great job by everyone.

post_text: In honor of Presidents Day, students at Buena Vista Elementary School researched different presidents throughout the history of the United States and then shared what they had learned with a “Living Museum” about the presidents on Friday, February 14, 2020. The students dressed as their presidents and presented facts and biographical information about their presidents’ lives and accomplishments. Please enjoy the images of these wonderful presentations.

post_text: Alamogordo High School Shockwave Team held their CO2 car competition Thursday, February 13, 2020. Students designed and built CO2 cars using information from the HAFB High Speed Test Track Engineer lectures and Physics and Calculus concepts they are learning this year. The results were as follows: Fastest time - Nate Black (1.097 seconds); Trevor Yelton (1.122 seconds); Most creative car - Bryson Kangas and Most Aerodynamic Design - Nate Black.

post_text: We are so excited to have 46 volunteers who are committed to spending an hour a week with 1st grade students who are reading below grade level. Our students will benefit from one-on-one sessions with an Adult Reading Coach using the Read2Win program. We are still taking volunteers and will hold another training session in December. Please contact us if you are interesting in serving our children!

post_text: Thank you to the United States Forest Service for harvesting this years U.S. Capitol Christmas Tree - right here in NM. Also, thanks to the New Mexico State Police for escorting it through the Land of Enchantment. We appreciate you stopping in Alamogordo, our kids loved it!

post_text: Today, students from Desert Star Elementary School visited the Alamo Senior Center. They sang and celebrated with our Seniors and recognized American WW II Veteran and Hero - Bonnie Stage. Great Job Kids!!!!
